result.execSummary:
The defendant Roberto Camacho Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Roberto Camacho Jr is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges. On one or more other charges, Roberto Camacho Jr was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Roberto Camacho Jr is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Roberto Camacho Jr was found guilty of Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).
  • Roberto Camacho Jr was found guilty of Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).
  • Roberto Camacho Jr was found guilty of Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).
  • Roberto Camacho Jr was found guilty of Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).
  • Roberto Camacho Jr was found guilty of Stalking [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.32(2).

Orders of the Court:
1. This court further finds that reasonable restrictions of the deft's ability to communicate are hereby necessary to prevent the further intimidation of witnesses. Accordingly, this Court Hereby Orders that all of the above-named deft's custody telephone, U.S. Mail, or visitation including by a third-party, such as a fellow inmate, while the deft remains in custody during this prosecution, SHALL BE COMPLETELY RESCINDED, with the exception of any communications to his atty, pursuant to the court's authority under 940.47(4) Wis. Stat.

2. This Court FURTHER ORDERS that the deft is to be confined, while in custody under this prosecution, in a location that where the Racine County Sheriff and/or Wisconsin Department of Corrections can assure this Court that this order is followed and strictly adhered to and ensuring that the deft has absolutely no access to telephone, U.S. Mail, or visitation, including third-party, such as a fellow inmate, except for contact with his atty, pursuant to the court's authority under 940.47(4) Wis Stat.
